PUBLIC WORKS/FORESTRY - Aid. Wisbrock (Bereitschaft, Clauss, Maserang)
Consideration of a request to amend an agreement with DEKA Corporation for HVAC maintenance and repair for City-owned buildings.
Staff is requesting that the Board consider amending the HVAC Maintenance and Repair Agreement with DEKA Corporation, approved in November of 2015 under Ordinance 3556, to include the new equipment installed by Trane and include the 2023 rates.

This agreement is for on-call, as needed, and routine maintenance operations of the HVAC equipment at the City of Fenton buildings, which includes spring and fall startups of the heating and cooling systems within the City's main buildings, an assessment of thecurrent systems, and hourly maintenance rates to perform repairs in a prompt fashion.

It is understood this agreement is only for the maintenance and service of the equipment. If any computer system malfunction occurs, the City would need to contract Trane for this type of work.

Based on the above, Staff is requesting that the Board amend the existing contract with DEKA to include the new Trane equipment as well as an updated pricing sheet for 2023 rates.

Mayor Maurath clarified this agreement would have DEKA perform spring and fall startups instead of the City's Building and Grounds Technician. Public Works Director Dan Howard replied Building and Grounds Technician has had assistance with startups since the beginning of his tenure with the City. Mayor Maurath asked for a list of what work the Building and Grounds Technician performs for the City. Public Works Director Dan Howard stated that the list would be endless.

Following discussion, Alderman Clauss made a motion to forward to the June Board of Aldermen meeting the consideration of a request to amend an agreement with DEKA Corporation for HVAC maintenance and repair for City-owned buildings. The motion was seconded by Alderman Maserang. Upon a vote being taken, it was announced that the motion was unanimously passed by the Committee.

