MISCELLANEOUS
Consideration of a request to allow for additional overflow vendors at the Farmers Market at a reduced rate.
As the new Farmers Market location is smaller offering only twelve (12) available vendor spaces protected under the pavilion (that will provide electric) at a cost of:

Full Season - 20 Weeks: Fee is $300 ($15 / week per booth)
Half Season- 10 Weeks: Fee is $200 ($20 / week per booth)
Weekly $20 / week per booth

Staff is asking for the Board to consider, only if all spaces are rented under the pavilion, to offer uncovered overflow space (no electric or generators will be permitted) in the grass next to the pavilion at a reduced rate and the vendor would need to provide their own tent. The proposed rate is:

Full Season - 20 Weeks: Fee is $200 ($10 / week per booth)
Half Season- 10 Weeks: Fee is $150 ($15 / week per booth)
Weekly $15 / week per booth

It is noted that there will be a maximum of four (4) spaces at the edge of the parking lot for vendors to set up a tent with direct access to their vehicle (such as meat vendors) as they are not allowed to drive on the grass, these spaces will be at the regular rate - no reduced rate will be offered.

Following discussion, Alderman Huels made a final motion to approve the consideration of a request to allow for additional overflow vendors at the Farmers Market at a reduced rate only if the pavilion is full. The motion was seconded by Alderman Cruts. Upon a vote being taken, it was announced that the motion was unanimously passed by the Board of Aldermen.

